<HEADLINE> Six Killed in Bangladesh Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed and 11
others seriously injured Tuesday in a road accident in southeast
Bangladesh, the official BSS news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Five people riding on a loaded truck died instantly when it
collided head-on with a Chittagong-bound passengers bus on the
Dhaka-Chittagong highway, police said.
</P>
<P>
A 10-year-old girl passenger of the bus died on the way to a
nearby health complex. 
</P>
