<HEADLINE> Olympic Champs Dolan, Poll Lose at World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dolan, the 400m individual medley gold medalist at the 1996
Atlanta Olympic Games, finished a distant seventh in three
minutes 55.87 seconds at the men's 400m freestyle final which was
won by German Joerg Hoffmann in 3:47.06.
</P>
<P>
"I did little for this meet. I think the U.S. Championships is
more important than this one, while the 400m free is not my
specialty event," Dolan said.
</P>
<P>
Dolan was also defeated in his strong event, 400m individual
medley, by Chinese Xie Xufeng. The American ranked third in the
event.
</P>
<P>
Poll, who claimed the title of women's 200m freestyle in Atl
anta, placed second in 8:29.58, losing to Chinese Chen Hua in
8:28.31.
</P>
<P>
While speaking of withdrawing from the 200m freestyle final
though she came first in the heats this morning, Poll said, "I am
preparing for the World Short Course Championships. When you give
up a little pie, others can take it away. I just want to exercise
in the women's longest event."
</P>
<P>
Seven out of eight golds in the women's events went to
Chinese. Chao Na recorded victory in 50m freestyle in 25.59
seconds while her teammate Lu Donghua dominated 50m backstroke,
timing at 28.79.
</P>
<P>
In 200m freestyle, Qin Caini beat Yang Lina to second place
with a winning time of 1:58.29.
</P>
<P>
The sole foreign women winner was Canadian Kelly Stefanshyn,
who underlined her prowess in 200m backstroke by defeating Rund
Cathleen of Germany.
</P>
<P>
In the men's events, Lenny Krayzelburg awarded swimming giant
United States a gold of 100m backstroke, clocking 53.49 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Denys Sylantyev of Ukraine bagged a gold of 200m butterfly in
1:56.51 and Germany's Krvppa Jens won 200m breaststroke in
2:13.06.
</P>
<P>
The 100m freestyle final was snatched by David Carter of
Australia who touched home in 49.88.
</P>
<P>
Chinese swimmers Zeng Qiliang, Zhang Qiang and Ouyang Kunpeng
won the men's 50m breaststroke, 50m butterfly and 100m individual
medley respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
