<HEADLINE> Kaklamanis Urges Peaceful Solution to Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Greek Parliament President
Apostolos Kaklamanis Tuesday called for a peaceful solution to the
crisis in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
During his talks with visiting Serb Deputy Prime Minister Ratko
Markovic, Kaklamanis expressed the grave concern of the prolonged
crisis in Kosovo, saying that the problem must be resolved through
peaceful means, chiefly on the initiative of the countries of the
region rather than powers outside the Balkans, according to the
semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA).
</P>
