<HEADLINE> French, Spanish Oil Groups Discover New Oilfield in Libya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The French oil group Total and its
partners Repsol of Spain and OMV have discovered a new oilfield in
the basin of Murzuk in southern Libya, said Total Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The oil reserve of the field is estimated at between 100 and
200 million barrels, said Repsol, which is the operator in the
field.
</P>
<P>
Primary tests showed that the quality of the oil, which is a
light kind, is very good, said the oil companies.
</P>
<P>
"The new discovery reinforces the stand of Total in the upper
area of Libya and confirms its interest in the basin of Murzuk,"
said Total in a communique.
</P>
<P>
Total, Repsol and OMV have been operating another oilfield in
the same basin since December 1996.
</P>
<P>
The oilfield, called El Sharara, is producing 140,000 barrels
of crude oil per day and is expected to produce 200,000 this year.
