<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-05 18:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Official Killed in Assassination Attempt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 5 (Xinhua) -- An Iranian judicial official was
killed Tuesday afternoon in an assassination attempt on the head
of Tehran province's justice department Ali Razini.
</P>
<P>
The state-run television reported that the official, whose
name was not known, was killed when Razini's car was attacked.
</P>
<P>
Armed assailants attacked Razini's car with hand grenades when
he left his office in the Khomeini Judicial Complex in downtown
Tehran for home, the Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Razini was injured slightly in the leg and his driver and two
passers-by were also wounded.
</P>
<P>
Razini, a well-known conservative figure in the country, was
rushed to hospital for treatment and his condition is stable, IRNA
said.
</P>
<P>
No individual or group has so far claimed responsibility for
the attack. 
</P>
</TEXT>
