<HEADLINE> Students Block Serra Leonean Ambassador's Residence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 5 (Xinhua) -- About 80 African students blocked
the entrance to the residence of the Sierra Leonean ambassador to
Russia Tuesday evening, Interfax reported.
</P>
<P>
However, a duty officer in Ambassador Melrose B. Kai-Banya's
residence denied the report.
</P>
<P>
"There were no students blocking the residence," said Rhoderick
Bernard, reached by telephone.
</P>
<P>
Interfax said the blockade was triggered by the death of a
Sierra Leonean student Tuesday morning from cancer.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of the protesting students accused the ambassador of
failing to perform her official duties as the embassy had refused
pleas for help from his fellow students four months before,
Interfax said.
</P>
<P>
Several students also broke into the Sierra Leonean Embassy on
Rublyov Avenue, Interfax said, quoting local law enforcement
sources.
</P>
<P>
A duty officer in the embassy, reached by telephone, refused to
give any comment.
</P>
<P>
"I don't know anything," he said. "We're resting. Please call
tomorrow morning." 
</P>
</TEXT>
