<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belgium Sees Reduced Budgetary Deficit in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The Belgian budget minister
said Tuesday that his country saw a record-low budgetary deficit
in the past year.
</P>
<P>
The 1998 deficit was 1.3 percent of the country's gross
domestic product, as against the government's prediction of 1.7
percent from last February and against the previous record low of
1.4 percent posted in 1966.
</P>
<P>
Budget Minister Herman van Rompuy described the low budget as
the "best performance ever achieved by the country's budget."
</P>
<P>
He added that the favorable deficit would be able to help the
country to achieve an economic growth of 2 percent in the past
fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
But Belgium was still up in the neck in debts. The country's
debt total as of December last year equaled to 116.5 percent of
its gross domestic product. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
