<HEADLINE> Blair Meets Bahrain Leader Over Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 5 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
met Bahrain's Prime Minister Sheikh Khalifa bin Sulman al-Khalifa
Tuesday to "compare notes" on how to tackle Iraqi leader Saddam
Hussein, said a British official said.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders met in the Seychelles, in the Indian Ocean, at
the tail end of Blair's holiday there, Downing Street revealed.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was important because of Bahrain's position as the
current representative of Arab states on the United Nations
Security Council, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting came amid fresh clashes between the United States
and Iraqi warplanes over Iraq.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Blair pledged to reaffirm the need to stand
up to Saddam, Downing Street said.
</P>
<P>
Blair is scheduled to visit South Africa from Wednesday.
</P>
