<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 20 Muscovites Die During New Year Holidays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Three people froze to death, 10
died in fires, and seven lost their lives in traffic accidents in
Moscow during the New Year holidays from January 1 to 4, Interfax
reported.
</P>
<P>
Over 200 fires were registered in the Russian capital in the
four days, Interfax said, quoting the State Anti-Fire Service.
</P>
<P>
The capital's traffic inspectorate has reported 50 major
traffic accidents, in which seven people died. Another 70,
including six children, were injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
