<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brussels Bourse Sets Record Again at Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The Brussels bourse Tuesday set
a second record of the year, closing 33.76 points up at 3,679.70
after gaining 0.93 percent upon Monday, the first trading day of
the year.
</P>
<P>
Monday's close already bettered the previous all-time high at
the Brussels bourse registered on July 20 last year when the
20-stock composite index Bel 20 closed at 3,632.07.
</P>
<P>
Economists were conservative in estimating the increase of the
volume of transactions in the bourse which is belittled by such
European gigantic stock exchanges as London, Frankfurt and Paris.
</P>
<P>
Monday was the first trading day of the year when transactions
and settlement started to use the single currency euro as the
accounting units. 
</P>
</TEXT>
