<HEADLINE> Kuwait Wishes Arab FM Meeting Success: Diplomat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait wishes the planned Arab
foreign ministers meeting a success, said Kuwaiti permanent
representative to the Arab League Abdel al-Kanei Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after meeting with Arab League chief
Esmat Abdel-Meguid, Al-Kanei said that Kuwait is the first country
to express readiness to take part in the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which is intended to discuss a call for an
emergency Arab summit on the U.S.- British military strikes
against Iraq, had been slated for last Wednesday, but was put off
to January 24 for better consultations and coordination.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti diplomat said that he discussed with Abdel-Meguid
the current Arab situation in general and necessary arrangements
for the proposed meeting.
</P>
<P>
On the agenda of the meeting, Al-Kanei said participants will
review the Arab stance on the Iraqi issue and its effects on the
Arab solidarity.
</P>
<P>
In what the United States claimed as a retaliation for Iraq's
defiance of the United Nations weapons inspections, the U.S. and
Britain launched four days of air attacks on Iraq on December
16-19.
</P>
<P>
Recently, Iraq has been criticizing other Arab countries for
delaying the foreign ministers meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
