<HEADLINE> President's Office Rapped for Mismanagement of Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KAMPALA, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan President's Office was
criticized Tuesday by a Parliamentary committee for poor accounting
standards in their use of funds.
</P>
<P>
The public accounts committee of parliament, which is chaired by
Augustine Ruzindana, said this when examining a report of the auditor-
general's report for the 1996-1997 financial year, Radio Uganda reported
Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
It said that as much as 13 billion Shillings (13 million U.S. Dollars)
of the office categorized as classified expenditure and rent payments for
office accommodation remained unaccounted for.
</P>
<P>
This raised several serious questions from the members of the committee,
 the report said, adding that the committee attaches great importance to
the accountability of funds and that any lack of seriousness will not be
tolerated.
</P>
<P>
All accounting officers yet to come before the committee were urged to
come prepared with all the evidence which is likely to be demanded.
</P>
<P>
The President's Office was represented by its Secretary Gabindadde
Musoke, the Principal Assistant Secretary Pius Bigirimana and other senior
officers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
