<HEADLINE> Iranian Passer-by Killed in Assassination Attempt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 5 (Xinhua) -- An Iranian passer-by died
Tuesday night after being injured in an assassination attempt on
the life of the head of Tehran province's justice department Ali
Razini, the Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The state-run television reported earlier that an Iranian
judicial official was killed in the assassination attempt.
</P>
<P>
However, the public relations office of Tehran province's
justice department denied the report and said that it was a
passer-by who was killed in the attack.
</P>
<P>
Unidentified armed assailants on a motorcycle attacked the
Patrol car carrying Razini with hand grenades when he left his
office in the Khomeini Judicial Complex in downtown Tehran for
home, IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
Razini, a well-known conservative figure in the country, was
injured slightly and had been rushed to hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
So far no one has claimed responsibility for the attack.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Interior Minister Abdolvahed Mousavi Lari Tuesday night
pledged to investigate the case and bring the criminals to
justice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
