<HEADLINE> Arab League Chief Invited to Attend EU Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Arab League Secretary General
Esmat Abdel-Meguid Tuesday received an invitation to attend an
upcoming foreign ministers meeting of the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
German Deputy Foreign Minister Von Hussel delivered the
invitation during a meeting with Abdel-Meguid, Egypt's Middle East
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Germany currently holds the EU's rotating presidency for the
first six months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The invitation, the first of its kind, is "an important
precedent", Abdel-Meguid said after meeting with the German
official.
</P>
<P>
The EU wishes to play a key role in resolving issues in the
Middle East, especially the peace talks between Arab countries and
Israel.
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid said that he discussed with Von Hussel world
issues of common concerns, especially those related to the Middle
East.
</P>
<P>
The German official praised the deeply-rooted relations between
Germany and Egypt, with which Germany seeks to enhance ties.
</P>
<P>
Germany is the biggest trading partner of Egypt among the EU
members and the second in offering aid to Egypt after the United
States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
