<HEADLINE> Botswana's Inflation Rises in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Botswana's year-on-year inflation
increased to 6.4 percent in December, over the 6.2 percent in November,
South African Press Association (SAPA) quoted the Bank of Botswana as
saying Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It said the all items consumer price index was up to 115.3 from 114.9
in the previous month. The base was 100 in November 1996.
</P>
<P>
The bank forecast further increases in inflation in the first few
months of 1999.
</P>
<P>
"This will reflect the effects of rising inflation in South Africa,
domestic salary increases and a rapid growth in credit and government
spending," the bank was quoted as saying.  
