<HEADLINE> Bus Explosion Kills 18 People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A bus explosion in northeast
China's Liaoning Province on January 4 killed 18 passengers,
according to official reports released today.
</P>
<P>
The local public security bureau reported the explosion
occurred at 23:00 (Beijing time) on Monday in Linghai killing 15
people immediatly. Three other victims died in the local hospital.
</P>
<P>
Local transportation officials said the explosion, which
rocked the middle section of the bus with more than 40
passengers, spread parts over a wide area and left a crater some
20 cm deep.
</P>
<P>
Local farmers rushed to the scene to render assistance. The
cause of the explosion remains under investigation. 
</P>
