<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Discuss Waste Disposal With Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will discuss with
Singapore the disposal of solid waste products, said Science,
Technology and Environment Minister Law Hieng Ding Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation in this area is necessary in light of reports that
lorries from Singapore were dumping such solid waste illegally in
Malaysia, Law told reporters after a cabinet meeting, according to
the Malaysian national news agency Bernama.
</P>
<P>
Law said his ministry has received reports from the Royal
Customs and Excise Department that lorries from Singapore had been
bringing in solid waste for dumping in Malaysia since last year.
</P>
<P>
Law said his ministry was waiting for further information
before taking action on the matter.
</P>
<P>
He said the relevant laws governing waste disposal would be
tightened to check such activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
