<HEADLINE> S. Leonean Rebels Enter Freetown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Sierra Leonean rebel troops have
entered the capital Freetown, after intensive fighting with the West
African peace-keeping force ECOMOG early Wednesday, the Sierra Leonean
government has confirmed.
</P>
<P>
A British Broadcasting Corporation (BBC) report quoted Sierra Leonean
Information Minister Julius Spencer as saying that though the situation is
very serious, it is going to be death with.
</P>
<P>
He urged residents in Freetown to stay at home, adding that "anyone
found on the streets will be considered as a rebel. "
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here, the rebels launched their attack on
Freetown at about 1:00am (0100GMT) Wednesday from the eastern suburb.
</P>
<P>
By 4:00am (0400GMT), the rebels have entered central and western
Freetown, but the rebels received strong resistance from the ECOMOG forces,
 the reports said.
</P>
<P>
In past few weeks, the rebels in Sierra Leone launched intensive
offensives, during which they seized major towns like Makeni and
Lunsar, and are reportedly in control over the northern half of the
country.
</P>
<P>
In an attempt to seize Freetown, the rebels have captured Port Loko and
other towns on the outskirts, though Port Loko was later retaken by the
peace-keepers.
</P>
<P>
In the last few days, ECOMOG warplanes and artillery had been bombing
rebel positions on the hills overlooking Freetown.
</P>
<P>
The rebels launched an attack on Hastings on the east outskirts Monday
and had overrun it to reach the eastern city gate before they were beaten
back by the ECOMOG. 
</P>
</TEXT>
