<HEADLINE> Organized Gang Commits Jewel Heist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The local public security bureau is investigating the case in
connection with a series of armed robberies in Chongqing, a
leading industrial city in southwest China, and Changsha, capital
of central China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The masked thieves brandished pistols during the robbery of a
jewelry store near the Wuhan Square Shopping Center in the Hankou
District at 18:58 (Beijing time) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The perpetrators exchanged heavy gunfire with local police
during their ensuing escape, leaving two police officers, one
soldier and three passers-by wounded. One of the six people
injured in the melee died a short time later. The gunmen fled the
scene in a taxi with gold jewelry valued at between 3-4 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The gang has reportedly killed several people during a number
of armed robberies in Chongqing, Changsha and various other
cities since 1994. The public security bureau has launched an
all-out effort to bring the culprits to justice.  
</P>
