<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Airport is One of World's Finest: Tung </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR),
Wednesday hailed the Hong Kong International Airport as one of
the finest in the world and one in which all Hong Kong people can
take pride.
</P>
<P>
During a two-hour tour of the new airport, Tung inspected both
cargo operations and passenger services and was shown various
improvements since its opening last July.
</P>
<P>
He said he was impressed by the smooth operation of airport
services and their high level of efficiency.
</P>
<P>
"I was happy to note that the airport was recently described
as one of the world's premier airports and was voted the annual
Critics' Choice Award by a leading international travel
magazine," he said.
</P>
<P>
While visiting the Super Terminal One cargo facility operated
by Hong Kong Air Cargo Terminals Limited (HACTL), Tung was told
that the facility was now handling an average of 5,000 tons of
cargo a day. At the height of the peak period last year, a total
of 6,500 tons of cargo were handled in one day.
</P>
<P>
Tung said he was pleased to see the airport cargo systems
operating smoothly since HACTL resumed full services last August.
</P>
<P>
Visiting the departure level of the passenger terminal
building, Tung said he was extremely pleased to see that there
had been significant improvements in services and facilities
since his last visit here in July 1998.
</P>
<P>
Airport Authority figures show that about 75 percent of
flights are departing on time or within 15 minutes of schedule.
Arriving passengers are waiting no longer than 15 minutes at
immigration counters and, on average, are able to reclaim baggage
within 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Tung said he was impressed by the fact that the airport
smoothly handled an average of around 100,000 passengers a day, a
record for the new airport, during the busy Christmas and New
Year period.
</P>
<P>
"This augurs very well for our busiest time of the year, which
is coming up shortly - Chinese New year," he said.
</P>
<P>
During his stay at the airport, Tung also visited retail ou
tlets, Airport Operations Control Center, the Baggage Sortation
Hall and the Security Screening Control Room.
</P>
<P>
Tung wrapped up his visit by meeting Airport Authority senior
management, and he encouraged them to keep up their good
performance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
