<HEADLINE> Fighting Erupts Again in Somali Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOGADISHU, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Amid the Holy month of Ramada, there
are reports of renewed heavy armed clashes in and around the southern port
town of Kismayu in the early Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the area said fierce fighting has begun between the
Majerten dominated clan militiamen of General Mohamed Saeed Hirsi Morgan
and those of the Marehan fighters for control of Kismayu Town.
</P>
<P>
According to sources from the region, the unexpected fighting has
started after the Marehan forces launched an attack against the
militia bases of the mainly Majerten men outside the town.
</P>
<P>
 Heavy shelling from mortar rounds, heavy machine guns, anti-aircraft
37 and 23 mm guns mounted on battle wagons, RPGs and assault rifles were
used during the exchange of fire by both sides early in the morning.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 people from both sides are reported to have died and more
than 50 others were wounded during this bitter armed confrontation.
However, eyewitnesses in Kismayu said the bodies of 12 people from both
sides were seen in the streets of the town after the confrontation
eased just before noon Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
 Independent sources, however, confirmed that one battle wagon
belonging to the Marehan Somali National Front (SNF) faction was destroyed
during the fighting before the SNF fighters were forces to retreat back to
their former militia bases outside the town.
</P>
<P>
The sources also said the Marehan fighters have captured the airport of
the town early in the morning before they were chased away by General
Morgan's men. The Marehan men are now being stationed at Gobwein village,
about 9 Km North of the city.
</P>
<P>
 The town of Kismayu, 500 Km South of Mogadishu, which had experienced
a relative calmness in recent days, was shocked Wednesday by the heavy
bombardment of the anti-aircraft machine guns and the mortar rounds which
hit several residential houses killing and wounding non-combatant civilians.
</P>
<P>
The supporters of General Morgan have claimed to have had the upper
hand and repulsed back the attack by the Marehan fighters.
</P>
<P>
General Morgan' s men also said that 10 men were captured from the
Marehan fighters as prisoners of war, a claim also admitted by the SNF
officials in Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
 A spokesman for the Marehan fighters here in Mogadishu said their men
have launched the attack on two fronts, one targeting the airport, while
the other aiming at capturing the former presidential palace of the town.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman furthermore said that his men had achieved military success
against those of the Mejertens in Kismayu by penetrating deep into the town
after crushing down the front defensive lines of General Morgan's men.
</P>
<P>
 The fighting for control of Kismayu has become one of the routine clan
 motivated clashes which would bring no success to anyone, but causes
destruction and heavy losses of human lives.
</P>
<P>
Kismayu town was calm Wednesday afternoon with the people bewildered by
the sudden attack of the Marehans which had caused a considerable damage
to the town.
</P>
<P>
All commercial activities in the main business centers of the town and
shops were closed because of the fighting with the people going to the main
hospital of the town to see their wounded ones and those dead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
