<HEADLINE> Railway Construction Proceeds Soundly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The fact that China increased
allocations for railway construction from 39.6 billion yuan in
1997 to 56.3 billion yuan in 1998 contributed greatly to the
nation's economic growth, according to Railway Minister Fu
Zhihuan.
</P>
<P>
 Fu made the comment during today's session of a related
national work conference.
</P>
<P>
 China completed new railway stretching 952 km. and
double-tracked railway line stretching some 1,127 km. during
1998, said Fu, adding that that construction of key projects in
southwest China is progressing smoothly.
</P>
<P>
 Statistics show a revival in the three-year slump in the
passenger transportation volume, with the 1998 volume growing 0.9
percent on an annual basis to 927 million.
</P>
<P>
 However, the freight transportation volume fell 5.3 percent
to end the year at 1.53 billion tons.
</P>
<P>
 Fu said the 1998 freight transportation volume for imports
and exports grew by 6.5 percent on the 1997 level to 9.22 million
tons.
</P>
<P>
 He also announced the delivery of the first order of metro
locomotives to Iran marked a major breakthrough in China's
exports of railway products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
