<HEADLINE> High Grade Heroin Seized at Hong Kong Airport High Grade Heroin Seized at Hong Kong Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Customs officers
seized 6.1 kilograms of No. 4 heroin worth 6.1 million HK dollars
(782,051 U.S. dollars) at the airport Tuesday, a spokesman for
the Customs and Excise Department said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Two men, aged 22 and 37, who were about to depart for Taiwan,
were arrested in connection with the seizure.
</P>
<P>
Acting on intelligence, officers of the Airport Investigation
Division and Customs Drug Investigation Bureau Tuesday morning
conducted an anti-narcotics operation to process outgoing
passengers at the departure level of the airport.
</P>
<P>
During the operation, two Hong Kong residents, who were about
to depart for Taiwan by an international flight, were intercepted
for search.
</P>
<P>
As a result, each of them was found body-packed with 2.9
kilograms and 3.2 kilograms of high grade heroin respectively.
Investigation into the case was still ongoing in order to track
down other syndicate members, the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
