<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Govt Troops Kill 7 Tamil Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
killed seven rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
in two separate clashes in the north of the country Monday and
Tuesday, a military spokesman said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ink Dewage, the spokesman, said government troops on patrol
east of Ampakamam Monday observed a group of rebels constructing a
bunker and engaged them with small arms, killing six rebels.
</P>
<P>
In another incident Tuesday at Oddusudan, government troops
observed a rebel bunker and fired with rocket-propelled grenades
and small arms, killing one rebel, said Dewage.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a war against the government
for a state of its own in the north and east of the country since
1983. Nearly 60,000 people are reported to have been killed in the
war. 
