<HEADLINE> CAE to Select Additional 120 Academicians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of
Engineering (CAE) announced here today that it will add 120 new
academicians this year.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Gaofeng, CAE vice president, said today at a conference
that selections will be made among senior engineers, researchers
and professors who have made major contributions and discoveries
in engineering science and technology and the application of new
inventions.
</P>
<P>
He said the candidates also include those of Chinese
nationality residing in Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He said at least one third of the newly selected academicians
will be experts and scholars under 60 years of age.
</P>
<P>
Song Jian, president of the CAE, said the CAE will focus on
providing consultations for central and local governments in
making policies for national economic development, social
development and major construction projects.
</P>
<P>
He said the CAE will promote international cooperation and
exchanges with foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
The CAE now has 437 academicians, including one from Hong Kong
and 12 from foreign countries. The selection of new academicians
is conducted once every two years.  
