<DOCNO> XIE19990106.0185 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 7 Tamil Rebels Nabbed While Making Bombs in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Seven Tamil rebels who were in
the process of manufacturing bombs to be brought to the capital of
Colombo have been arrested by a team of army officers in Eastern
province of Sri Lanka, reports reaching here said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The raid last Sunday also arrested a police constable who had
been with the Tamil rebels at the time, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The suspects were arrested in an isolated house in Palaminmadu,
Batticaloa, while manufacturing the bombs, said the reports,
adding that the arrested policeman is from Tricomalee, also in the
Eastern province of the country.
</P>
<P>
The suspects have been identified as key members of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) responsible for
dispatching bombs to Colombo, the reports noted.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE used the police constable as a pawn for the smooth
transport of bombs to Colombo, a senior police officer was quoted
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting the government since 1983 for a
separate state in the north and east of the island nation.
</P>
</TEXT>
