<HEADLINE> China to Export More Electronic, Machinery Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- China plans to export 40
billion U.S. dollars in machinery products in the year 2000, the
"China Trade News" reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
 Officials from the machine building industry said they
were determined that China would grow into a major exporter for
machinery over the next few years.
</P>
<P>
They made the vow at the opening session of a national
conference focused on the sector's future, and stressed that
China is already one of the world's major machine-building
nations. They said they were planning to position the sector to
help it develop.
</P>
<P>
The machine-building industry is one of the most vigorous
growth points in China's industrial sector, with an average
annual growth rate of 14 percent over the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, China's machinery exports yielded about 30 billion
U.S. dollars in foreign exchange revenues which accounted for
some 20 percent of total exports.
</P>
<P>
Its output of power generating equipment ranks fourth in
the world, with the output of machine-tools holding sixth
place.  
</P>
