<HEADLINE> Argentina Beats Venezuela in South American U-20 Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion
Argentina opened up their campaign with a victorious note when
they beat Venezuela 4-1 at the 19th South American U-20 Soccer
Championship in Mar del Plata on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Trailing 1-0 at half-time, Argentina launched all-out attacks
in the second half, pounding the Venezuela defense fiercely.
</P>
<P>
Their effort paid off when Duscher opened up the scoring in
the 60th minute, followed by two goals by his teammates.
</P>
<P>
Striker Aimar slotted one in the last minute to complete the
drubbing.
</P>
<P>
Ten South American teams are competing here, with the top four
placers qualifying for the World Youth Soccer Championship to be
held in Nigeria in April.
</P>
<P>
In the opener of the tournament, Chile defeated Ecuador 2-0.
</P>
