<HEADLINE> Top-ten Industry, Economic News Stories Selected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The fight against last year's
devastating summer floods has been ranked first of the top-ten
economic and industry news stories selected by the China Industry
Newspaper Association.
</P>
<P>
Second on the list is the central government's decision to
extend the land contract system for farmers for a further 30
years, followed by sweeping reform schemes of the central bank
system, and the implementation of active fiscal policies.
</P>
<P>
China's success in keeping the nation's currency renminbi
stable amid the Asian financial crisis and the nationwide efforts
to provide basic living standards for the increasing numbers of
laid-off workers as a result of the restructuring of state-owned
enterprises take fifth and sixth places, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Other top stories include the deaths of 27 people who consumed
substandard alcoholic drinks made in Shanxi Province, the
tax-evasion case involving renowned pop singer Mao Aming and the
rapid progress in the telecommunications industry.
</P>
<P>
China recorded a total foreign trade volume of 325 billion US
dollars in 1998, ranking 10th in the world, and this is the last
of the top ten stories.  
</P>
