<HEADLINE> S. African Urged to Have Flu Vaccination 017 This story is from XH-PC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- South Africa is very much likely to
be attacked by killer Sydney flu, medical experts have warned.
</P>
<P>
The Star daily reported Wednesday that medical departments are advizing
people in the country to have flu vaccination to guard against the killer
virus before winter comes this year.
</P>
<P>
According to Stephen Toovey, director of Medical Information, about 5,
000 South Africans died of flu last year.
</P>
<P>
Toovey urged people to get a vaccination this year, saying that it was
the only way to prevent the virus.
</P>
<P>
It was reported the epidemic has already hit Britain with thousands of
people contracting the H3N2 strain of Sydney flu over the Christmas period.
</P>
<P>
The strain can be fatal in the elderly and the very young, as well as
those with respiratory disorders, cardiovascular disease and poorly
functioning immune systems.
</P>
<P>
Based upon their recent studies, South African medical experts said
pregnant women are more prone to the symptoms of flu, and that the current
vaccination can be administered to them safely from the fourth month
onwards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
