<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Credit Guarantees Help Private Economy In Southwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, January 6 (Xinhua)-- China's first private business
credit guarantee service center is helping private businesses in
Guiyang, capital city of Guizhou Province, to get easier access
to bank loans.
</P>
<P>
The Guiyang Reflection Film Co. Ltd., which is a member of the
Guiyang Credit Guarantee Center designed specially for private
businesses, recently borrowed a much-needed 1-million yuan loan
from the city commercial bank in just three days, something that
would have been almost impossible without the center sharing its
financial risk.
</P>
<P>
China is encouraging the private sector more by increasing
credit. For many small and medium-sized private companies,
however, it is still hard to get a mortgage or find guarantees
for a bank loan. But, with the new credit guarantee service, the
problem is more readily solved, according to Xiao Yue, a Guiyang
Administration for Industry and Commerce official.
</P>
<P>
The center got authorization from the People's Bank of China
Guiyang Branch and is now selecting 50,000 member firms from a
list of 72,900 businesses to build its trust fund up to 5 billion
yuan. The city government has also allocated 3 million yuan to
help the business.
</P>
<P>
The banking sector has shown its trust in the center's ability
and has offered a favorable credit rating to allow it to provide
1.5 billion yuan in loans to private firms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
