<HEADLINE> Dokic Beats Sanchez-Vicario  (Reopen) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Australia's world junior No.1
Jelena Dokic downed world No. 4 Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario in
straight sets at the Hopman Cup tennis tournament in Perth,
Australia on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen-year-old Dokic played the game of her life to beat
Sanchez Vicario 6-3 6-2 and give Australia an unexpected 1-0 lead
in its clash with top seed Spain.
</P>
<P>
Dokic exploited the French Open champion's misfiring forehand
and broke her serve seven times.
</P>
<P>
Dokic took just 68 minutes to beat Sanchez Vicario who is
ranked 337 places above her.
</P>
<P>
The win was a dramatic turnaround from her 6-1 6-0 defeat at
the hands of South Africa's Amanda Coetzer just three days
earlier.
</P>
<P>
"I played much better and I was thinking more and took my
time," Dokic said.
</P>
<P>
"I knew from the first game I would have to play well to beat
her. I was nervous in the first set, but I played well and I am
happy that I won."
</P>
<P>
Also on Wednesday afternoon, Australian Mark Philippoussis
defeated Carlos Moya 6-4 7-6 in the men's singles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
