<HEADLINE> Famine Looms Large in N. Kenya Due to Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
 NAIROBI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A famine disaster looms large in North
Eastern Province of Kenya as the effects of drought start to bite.
</P>
<P>
 Over one million people in the province are faced with an intense
shortage of food and water, the East African Standard newspaper reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
 The government has already started distributing famine relief food to
alleviate the acute food shortage that has been caused by the drought,
Minister of State Gideon Ndambuki was quoted as saying on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
For about two months, the short rains have failed in the major
district of
Garissa, Wajir, Moyale, Mandera, Marsabit and Isiolo as the reality of
starvation hit the province, said the report.
</P>
<P>
 An official with the World Food Program (WFP) also confirmed that the
 famine situation in the province is real and urgent action is needed to
curtail the calamity.
</P>
<P>
 "We are aware of the situation in the province though we cannot give a
 substantial account just yet though we are meant to believe that Mandera
is the worst-hit," said the official.  
</P>
</TEXT>
