<HEADLINE> North China's Private Business Invests in Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A privately financed 3.3
km-long railway is to be constructed in north China's Shanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
 The railway will be an exclusive line for Shanxi Sunshine
Coking (Group) Co. Ltd., a private enterprise based in Shanxi's
Hejin city and with fixed assets totaling 50 million yuan and a
workforce of 400.
</P>
<P>
Xue Dianmin, Sunshine's chairman, said that the railway line
will help lower transport costs and increase efficiency, and that
the 27 million-yuan project has received support from the local
government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
