<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-06 07:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Soldier Wounded in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, January 6 (Xinhua) -- An Israeli soldier was seriously
wounded in a bomb attack in south Lebanon on Tuesday, the National
Broadcasting Network radio reported Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The radio quoted security sources as saying that a roadside
bomb was detonated by guerrillas of the Iranian-backed Hezbollah,
or Party of God, when an Israeli convoy passed by the Arnoun
village in the eastern sector of the Israeli-occupied border zone.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the convoy were en route to an army base
near Beaufort Castle, a crusader fortress in the zone.
</P>
<P>
The wounded soldier was evacuated to hospital in Israel, the
radio added.
</P>
<P>
This is the first casualty the Israeli occupation force
suffered in the region since the start of this year. Last year, a
total of 24 Israeli soldiers were killed in south Lebanon while 42
Lebanese guerrillas lost their lives in conflicts.
</P>
<P>
Israel carve out a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon
in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from Lebanese
guerrillas cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by
Hezbollah has been fighting to oust Israeli troops from the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
