<DOCNO> XIE19990106.0240 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Steffi Graf: Play Well and Enjoy Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Former World No.1 tennis
player Steffi Graf said here on Wednesday that she cares more
about playing well and enjoying the game than rankings.
</P>
<P>
Graf, who arrived here Tuesday night after a one-day delay due
to bad weather, will play in a three-day tournament along with
several top women players including Venus and Serena Williams and
Anna Kournikova.
</P>
<P>
"In the last few weeks I was able to train very well ... and I
hope I can keep on going and it is good for me to have a couple
of matches to start the year," Graf told a press conference after
her first training session before the tournament.
</P>
<P>
"I need a few tournaments to gain confidence and get in the
rhythm," said Graf, who was ranked No.1 for a record 377 weeks
and is currently on 9th in WTA rankings.
</P>
<P>
"It took me quite a while to start off the year after a lot of
setbacks," including the wrist and knee operations. But now she
has "nothing to worry about physically since she went out at the
end of last year and played."
</P>
<P>
Asked about the possibility of retaining world's No.1, the
30-year-old German said it is something that she doesn't "worry
too much about." "For me it's about enjoying."
</P>
<P>
Having won 106 career titles including 21 Grand Slam events,
four Australian Open titles, five French Open tiles, seven
Wimbledon titles and five U.S. Open titles, Graf said: "I want to
play well and that's my main goal."
</P>
<P>
"It is a thrill to be in the court playing to tough players
and getting the atmosphere of the crowd -- they are really behind
me. I still enjoy so much. That's why I am still around."
</P>
<P>
Graf denied the rumor that she will retire soon.
</P>
<P>
Playing in the "Super-Power" Challenge Cup in Hong Kong for a
second time, Graf said she is happy to visit places she has been
to and will spend some time in local antique markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
