<HEADLINE> Tebbutt Defeats Kuerten in Men's Hardcourt Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Australian Michael Tebbutt
eliminated 1997 French Open winner Gustavo Kuerten in a thrilling
upset at the Australian Hardcourt Tennis Championship in
Adelaide, Australia on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Wildcard Tebbutt, ranked 122 in the world, defeated the
Brazilian 6-7 (7-2), 7-6 (7-5), 7-6 (7-3) to advance to the
quarter finals.
</P>
<P>
The lefthander won three points on Kuerten's serve in the
final tiebreak to end the two and a half hour match in sweltering
conditions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Slovakian Dominik Hrbaty also progressed to the
quarter-finals after German qualifier Oliver Gross withdrew
because of a lower back injury.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, second seed Thomas Enqvist eliminated German David
Prinosil 6-2, 6-3 to advance to the quarter-finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
