<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Get 4.4M Dollar Loan From Sweden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will receive 35 million
Swedish kroner equivalent to 213.5 million taka (4.4 million U.S.
dollars) as additional loan from Sweden, according to an official
press release reaching here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
An agreement to this effect was signed between the two sides in
Dhaka Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This is in addition to Sweden's contribution to the 40 million
Swedish kroner or 250 million taka (5.15 million dollars) provided
earlier as loan for infrastructure development under a rural
employment sector program.
</P>
<P>
The main objective of the project is to improve the road
standard on feeder roads type-B and construct bridges in
Bangladesh's five districts.
</P>
<P>
The implementation of the project will help improve the rural
communication network, increase agricultural production, expand
trade and commerce and thereby generate employment opportunities
in these districts, the release said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
