<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Secret Agents Involved in Iran's Recent Murders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Intelligence Ministry
has announced that some of its agents were behind the recent
mysterious murders of an opposition leader and several dissident
writers in Tehran, local daily Iran News reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Regrettably, a few of our own devious colleagues ... were
among those who committed these crimes," said a statement issued
by the ministry Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the ministry has succeeded in identifying
and arresting the network responsible for the killings and handed
them over for prosecution. But it did not mention how many people
were arrested in the connection.
</P>
<P>
In November and December, leader of the Iran Nation Party
Darius Forouhar and his wife were stabbed to death at home and at
least two dissident writers were then mysteriously killed in
Tehran.
</P>
<P>
The killings aroused grave concern of the government and
President Mohammad Khatami ordered the ministries of interior and
intelligence to form a special committee to probe into the cases.
</P>
<P>
In its statement, the Intelligence Ministry said it condemns
any crime against any human being and any threat against the
safety and security of citizens.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also vowed to uproot the elements instigating
political violence and guarantee security in the country and
continue to investigate the murders in order to identify other
culprits involved in the cases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990106.0248 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Providing Commercial Services For Eastern Chinese Port City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Ningbo, an important port city
on China's eastern coast, has a new project to upgrade a number
of commercial companies and to develop large markets to improve
its commercial services and raise economic returns.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government has begun a "Six-tens" program by
establishing 10 markets for special commodities, 10
vegetable-growing bases, 10 commercial group companies, 10
shopping centers, 10 supermarkets with chain stores, and 10
commercial blocks.
</P>
<P>
The project is going smoothly, according to a local official,
who says that the city now has some companies which are leaders
in their field, including the largest computer-run vegetable
growing center in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
