<HEADLINE> The following are major news items in leading Kenyan newspapers Wednesday: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Kenya Times:
</P>
<P>
 -- The National Bank of Kenya Tuesday announced a freeze on further
lending to enable the bank to settle after being hit by a run on its
deposits
last year.
</P>
<P>
Daily Nation:
</P>
<P>
 -- Congolese rebel leader Ernest Wamba dia Wamba said Tuesday
that a threatened split in the coalition fighting to oust President Laurent
 Kabila had been averted after talks with senior Ugandan and Rwandan
officials.
</P>
<P>
 -- Sudan has imposed a new dress code on women requiring them to wear
Islamic attire and a head scarf and will deploy public-order police to
ensure that it is observed, the official news agency Suna said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
 East African Standard:
</P>
<P>
 -- Namibian President Sam Nujoma was Tuesday due to interrupt his
summer holidays for a meeting with Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe, the
Namibian Broadcasting Corporation reported.  
</P>
