<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed higher here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 17 points higher at 2,132 with a
turnover of 115 million NZ dollars (61.5 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leading stocks, Fletcher Energy was the biggest
winner, up 17 cents to 402 cents, followed by Air New Zealand up 9
to 269 cents.
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Building and Fletcher Paper put on 7 cents each to 315
and 133 cents respectively, Fletcher Forest 4 to 73 cents, Telecom
3 to 850 cents, Brierley Investments 2 to 47 cents and Carter Holt
Harvey 1 cent to 183 cents.
</P>
<P>
AMP went against the trend, falling 20 cents to 2,390 cents,
followed by Auckland Airport, down 7 cents to 269 cents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
