<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines' Inflation Up 9.7 percent in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Despite the financial crisis and
big typhoons, the year-on-year inflation rate in the Philippines
went up 9.7 percent in 1998, well within the government target of
9.25-9.75 percent, the National Statistics Office said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In its monthly report released here, the office said the
inflation rate in December slowed down slightly to 10.4 percent
from 11.2 percent in November, bringing the average for 1998 to
9.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
All the commodity groups recorded lower inflation rates in
December, it said.
</P>
<P>
The office said that the rates for food, beverages and tobacco
slowed down to 11.2 percent in December from 12.2 percent in
November; clothing, 7.2 percent from 7.4 percent; housing and
repairs, 9.8 percent from 10 percent; fuel, light and water, 6.3
percent from 6.5 percent; and services, 11.5 percent from 12.5
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
