<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Denmark's Oil Output Hits Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Denmark's oil output in 1998
was up 3 percent from the previous year to an all-time high of
annual 11.8 million metric tons, said reports reaching here
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Danish officials were quoted as saying that the increase, from
the state-owned oil field in the North Sea, was the result of
applying new technologies on existing wells, rather than expanded
operations.
</P>
<P>
Surplus after addressing domestic needs, one-third of the
annual oil production went to the international market in 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
