<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albania's Population: Urban Up, Rural Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Figures released by the Institute of Statistics (INSTAT) show
that the urban population in Albania in 1997 reached 1,526,000,
or 45.9 percent of the nation's total 3,324,000 inhabitants,
while the rural population was reduced by 54.1 percent of the
total.
</P>
<P>
In 1990, the urban population stood at 1,176,000, or 36.1
percent of the total population, while the rural registration was
reported as 2,079,900, or 63.9 percent of the total inhabitants
in the nation.
</P>
<P>
The INSTAT attributed the ratio changes between the urban and
rural population to the free movement of inhabitants.
</P>
<P>
The urban population in 1997 went up by 388,000, or 34
percent, compared with that of 1989, the INSTAT added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
