<HEADLINE> Stimulant Drugs Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities seized
274,000 stimulant amphetamine tablets in the country's eastern
Shan state last December, the official newspaper The New Light of
Myanmar reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The seizure was made by a combined team of regional
intelligence unit, armymen and police who raided two houses in
Meileikpakaw village in Tachilek on December 5.
</P>
<P>
