<HEADLINE> China Tapping East China Sea Oil Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 6 (Xinhua) -- China has committed itself to
exploring oil resources in the East China Sea and recently found
a 16-billion-cubic-meter natural gas reserve in the sea east of
the city of Wenzhou in Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
High-yield oil and gas reserves have been discovered in the
region. The Pinghu oilfield, with 26 billion cubic meters of gas
reserves, will begin to provide 1.2 million cubic meters of
natural gas every day for Shanghai in February.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 billion tons of crude oil are estimated offshore
in the East China Sea, which could help solve the energy shortage
in the developed eastern areas of China, experts say.
</P>
<P>
The Chunxiao oilfield, which has natural gas reserves of more
than 100 billion cubic meters, now provides ample energy for
major industrialized cities along the coast in Zhejiang
Province. 
</P>
