<HEADLINE> China to Standardize Levy Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A senior government official
said here today that China's financial and taxation reform in
1999 will focus on the standardization of levy management.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Finance Xiang Huaicheng said at a press conference
this morning that the reform on the levying system will be first
carried out on roads and vehicles, which have been involved in
serious illegal and irrational charging problems.
</P>
<P>
He said that efforts will be made to implement the reform
according to law as early as possible within this year.
</P>
<P>
The financial authorities are also designing a plan for rural
levying reform, which aims to clarify taxes and fees, rationalize
revenue distribution and cut the burden on rural residents in
three years, he said.
</P>
<P>
In 1998 China revoked a total of 727 items of illegal or
irrational funds and fees, which helped cut a total of some 37
billion yuan as burdens on enterprises within the year.  
