<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albania Urges Unification of Kosovo Albanian Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Rexhep
Mejdani, in his first open meeting with the separatist Kosovo
Liberation Army (KLA) leaders on Tuesday, urged the unification
of rival ethnic Albanian political groups in Serbia's province of
Kosovo in order to find an acceptable political solution to the
Kosovo issue.
</P>
<P>
During a two-hour meeting with KLA political representative
Adem Demaci, Mejdani said, "It is time to have an authoritative
voice for this dramatic reality in Kosovo."
</P>
<P>
Mejdani said a pan-Albanian group should be found for the
factious Kosovo Albanian political community, which has so far
failed to agree on a common strategy for resolving the Kosovo
issue.
</P>
<P>
Mejdani expressed his readiness to discuss and boost contacts
with all forces in Kosovo to reach a more realistic position.
</P>
<P>
Albanian Foreign Minister Paskal Milo and People's Assembly
speaker Skender Gjinushi made a similar call in separate meetings
with Demaci later on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Milo called on Kosovo Albanian factions to coordinate their
positions and take joint political actions internationally so as
to find a fair settlement for the Kosovo conflict.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, Milo said he and Demaci agreed that the
only way to end the Kosovo conflict is through a combination of
diplomacy and decisive intervention by the international
community including the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO).
</P>
<P>
Demaci said the KLA is willing to solve the Kosovo crisis
through peaceful means, but also determined to stage non-peaceful
resistance.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for the Albanian leaders to meet KLA
representatives. Albania has repeatedly denied having relations
with the KLA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
