<HEADLINE> China to Cut Import Duty for 1,014 Tax Items </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- China has decided to cut the
import duty for 1,014 tax items, including textiles, toys and
forestry products, effective on January 1, according to Minister
of Finance Xiang Huaicheng.
</P>
<P>
Xiang told a press conference this morning that the import tax
rates for these three categories of goods will be lowered by
eight to 78 percent on average. 
