<DOCNO> XIE19990106.0309 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Net International Reserves Decline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Bank Indonesia's net
international reserves dropped by 374 million U.S. dollars to 14.1
billion U.S. dollars as of December 31 from the December 23 level
of 14.43 billion dollars, the Jakarta Post reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The central bank said in its weekly report that the decrease
was due to repayment of part of the government's foreign debt and
the payment of a quarterly contribution to the International
Monetary Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
The central bank said that net reserves remained above the
minimum level of 10.71 billion dollars set by the IMF.
</P>
<P>
Bank Indonesia reported that gross foreign exchange reserves,
which include net foreign exchange reserves plus outstanding
foreign exchange contracts, fell by 360.8 million dollars to 23.6
billion dollars during the same week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
