<DOCNO> XIE19990106.0320 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Quake Rocks Padang, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A tectonic earthquake measuring
4.1 on the Richter scale rocked Padang and its surrounding areas
in Indonesia's West Sumatera province on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the geophysical station in Padang Panjang, the
quake has its epicenter 30 kilometers deep in the Mentawai strait,
some 60 kilometers west of the provincial capital of Padang.
</P>
<P>
When the tremor struck for about 25 seconds, the Muslims doing
their early evening prayers appeared not to have been disturbed,
Antara News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the geophysical station, an average of 60 quakes
hit the province each year, with the strongest measuring 6 on the
Richter scale in April last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
